{"lemma":"مُرّ","slug":"مُرّ","root":"م.ر.ر","root_slug":"م-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُرّ","root":"مرر","pos":"V","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38360","n38369","n43544","n38370"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass, to elapse, to go by, to cross"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go through(?) (constructed with ب (b))","examples":[{"text":"فهل تمر بمشاكل كهذه.","english":"Are you going through problems like this."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bitter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"passing, passage, going by, transit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shovel, spade"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bitter"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"severe"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sharp"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"painful"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"myrrh, the dried sap of Commiphora myrrha"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"myrrh, the plant Commiphora myrrha","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dandelion (Taraxacum officinale sensu lato)","tags":["collective","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic מרא / ܡܪܐ (marrā, “shovel”), from Akkadian 𒄑𒈥 (GEŠ-MAR /⁠marru⁠/). .\n\nCompare Hebrew מַר (mar), Classical Syriac ܡܪܝܪܐ (marrīrā), Akkadian 𒋀 (marru), and Ugaritic 𐎎𐎗 (mr)."},"ipa":["/mar.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38360","headword_ar":"مَرَّ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~N","text_ar":"مَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamar~N","text_ar":"مَمَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruwrN","text_ar":"مُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, passed; passed by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond; went; went on; proceeded; passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over; went away; passed away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAza","text_ar":"جَازَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY","text_ar":"مَضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astmr~","text_ar":"استمرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, Mgh, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"مَرَّ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amoru","text_ar":"الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astmr~","text_ar":"استمرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (A, Mgh, Msb, TK.) The saying in the Kur, [vii. 189,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamalato HamolFA xafiyfFA famar~ato bihi","text_ar":"حَمَلَتْ حَمْلًا خَفِيفًا فَمَرَّتْ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bh","text_ar":"به"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astmr~t","text_ar":"استمرّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) which is another reading, (Bd,) i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She bore a light burden"},{"kind":"text","text":"in her womb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went with it, and moved from place to place, and rose and sat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not being oppressed by its weight: (A:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went on with it in the same course"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went and came with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of its lightness: (Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose and sat with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, Bd,) not being oppressed by its weight: (Zj:) so accord. to both the readings mentioned above: (Bd:) by the burden being meant the impregnating fluid. (Bd, Jel, TA.) ―         -b2-  [It is also said of water, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It ran,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed."},{"kind":"text","text":"And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"مَرَّتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind passed along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blew."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a bihi","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"مَرَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb,) but the former is more common than the latter, (Mughnee, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) for which the BenooYarbooa say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mir~a Elyh","text_ar":"مِرَّ عليه"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ahu","text_ar":"مَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [respecting which see what follows the explanation,] (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~N","text_ar":"مَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamar~N","text_ar":"مَمَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruwrN","text_ar":"مُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimotar~a","text_ar":"اِمْتَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimotar~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"اِمْتَرَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, by him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijotaAza","text_ar":"اِجْتَازَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAza Ealayohi","text_ar":"جَازَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAwazahu wa*ahaba","text_ar":"جَاوَزَهُ وَذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a verb trans. by means of a particle and without a particle: or in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ahu","text_ar":"مَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the particle may be suppressed: Jereer says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tamur~uwna Ald~iyaAra walamo taEuwjuwA\n                     \n                     \n                        kalaAmukumu EalaY~a A_i*FA HaraAmu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye pass by the dwellings without turning aside and alighting: the speaking to you is therefore forbidden to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but it is said that the true reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotumo biAld~iyaAri","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُمْ بِالدِّيَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye have passed by the dwellings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: which shows that he feared to make the verb trans. without a particle: IAar says, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a zayodFA","text_ar":"مَرَّ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a bihi","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed by Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"], without being elliptical, but as being properly trans.; but IJ, allowing this, says that it is not a phrase commonly obtaining. (M, TA.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"مَرَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"across, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a EalaY Aljisori","text_ar":"مَرَّ عَلَى الجِسْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2700},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over the bridge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dyke."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ik~iynu EalaY Haloqi Al$~aApi","text_ar":"السِّكِّينُ عَلَى حَلْقِ الشَّاةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The knife passed across the throat of the sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  [Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a period of time)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed over him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a calamity)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came upon him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. of the latter signification below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~N","text_ar":"مُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a bihi","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amar~ahu","text_ar":"اَمَرَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", trans. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ahu","text_ar":"مَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as trans. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the aor. is"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~a","text_ar":"مُرَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His bile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gall, became roused."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murirotu","text_ar":"مُرِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I suffered an attack of bile"},{"kind":"text","text":"], from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almir~apu","text_ar":"المِرَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murirotu bihi","text_ar":"مُرِرْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umar~u","text_ar":"اُمَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~N","text_ar":"مَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mir~apN","text_ar":"مِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, T, M, K,) the latter of which [in the CK written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ap","text_ar":"مَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in the T, M, &c."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mir~ap","text_ar":"مِرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and expressly said in the TA to be with kesr,] is also a simple subst., (T,) or, as Lh says in one place,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mir~N","text_ar":"مِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mir~apN","text_ar":"مِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a simple subst., (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gall, overcame me"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. referring to food]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TK","Bd","Jel","Zj","TA","T","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n38369","headword_ar":"مَرٌّ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~apN","text_ar":"مَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2701}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43544","headword_ar":"مَرٌّ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spade;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the present day;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHaApN","text_ar":"مِسْحَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one works in land of seed-produce:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M and K, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlN","text_ar":"بَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"handle thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAv","text_ar":"مِحْرَاث"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fire-shovel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"six~iynN","text_ar":"سِخِّينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing with which one works in earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M"]},{"entry_id":"n38370","headword_ar":"مُرٌّ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bitter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;) contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulowN","text_ar":"حُلْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mariyrN","text_ar":"مَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumir~N","text_ar":"مُمِرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~apN","text_ar":"مُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoraArN","text_ar":"اَمْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M,) and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAy^iru","text_ar":"مَرَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to rule, (Msb,) because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~apN","text_ar":"مُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvapu AlT~aEomi","text_ar":"خَبِيثَةُ الطَّعْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad-tasted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbyvp","text_ar":"خبيثة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAy^ivu","text_ar":"خَبَايِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqolapN mur~apN","text_ar":"بَقْلَةٌ مُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bitter leguminous plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha*ihi","text_ar":"هَذِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqolapu mino A^amoraAri Albuqowli","text_ar":"البَقْلَةُ مِنْ اَمْرَارِ البُقْولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This leguminous plant is"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bitter leguminous plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapN mur~apN","text_ar":"شَجَرَةٌ مُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bitter tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarN maraAy^iru","text_ar":"شَجَرٌ مَرَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the only instance of the kind except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAy^iru","text_ar":"حَرَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~apN","text_ar":"حُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Suh, in Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr","text_ar":"حر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riEoYu bnY fulaAnK Almur~ataAni","text_ar":"رِعْىُ بنى فُلَانٍ المُرَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in two copies of the S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almur~ayaAni","text_ar":"المُرَّيَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pasturage of the sons of such a one is the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bitter tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alA='","text_ar":"اَلا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bitter plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyH","text_ar":"شِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) [For another application of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almur~ataAni","text_ar":"المُرَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amar~a","text_ar":"اَمَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Hence also, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almur~u","text_ar":"المُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Myrrh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain medicine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abir","text_ar":"الصَّبِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloes"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"useful for cough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when sucked"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotiHolaAbFA","text_ar":"اـِسْتِحْلَابًا"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for the sting of the scorpion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when applied as a plaster,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for worms of the intestines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when taken into the mouth in a dry state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"licked up from the palm of the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also said to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abiru","text_ar":"الصَّبِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoraArN","text_ar":"اَمْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ey$","text_ar":"عيش"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~N","text_ar":"مُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bitter life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: like as one says [of the contr.],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulowN","text_ar":"حُلْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~ato Ealayohi A^amozaArN","text_ar":"مَرَّتْ عَلَيْهِ اَمْزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Afflictions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calamities"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_